# Project: Circle

## What We're Building

A fullscreen React app split into 4 quadrants by a cross (two dividing lines meeting at dead centre).

At the centre of the screen sits a **circular path**. 4 words are placed on that circle, evenly spaced (12, 3, 6, 9 o'clock positions), one word per quadrant.

The **entire thing rotates slowly** as one unified object — the cross lines and the 4 words together — spinning from the dead centre point of the screen.

## Key Visual Rules

- Screen always fills the full viewport, divided into 4 equal white quadrants
- The cross divider lines are a single 1px internal stroke
- The circular path and 4 words sit exactly at the centre
- Everything rotates from `transform-origin: center center` of the viewport
- Words stay on the circle as it spins — they are glued to the circular path
- Rotation is slow and continuous

## Tech Stack

- React + Vite + TypeScript
- GSAP for animation (rotating the whole container from centre)
- Dev server: `npm run dev` on port 5555
- Python static server: `python3 serve.py` on port 5555
